Commemorations of Institution of Takeshima Day in Japan Assailed 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, February 26 (KCNA) -- South Koreans of different social standings denounced the Shimane Prefectural authorities of Japan for holding "commemorations of the first anniversary of the institution of the Takeshima Day", according to south Korean KBS and CBS. 
 The authorities enacted a draft law on instituting the "Takeshima (Tok Islet) Day" in last March and held commemorations of its first anniversary on Feb. 22.
 The All People Solidarity for Defending Tok Islet held press conferences in front of the Japanese embassy in Seoul on Feb. 21 and 22 and branded the commemorations held by the Japanese government and the Shimane Prefectural authorities as an act of invading an inviolable territory of the Korean nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The organization threatened that the south Koreans will conduct a campaign to boycott the Japanese goods if Japan's claim to Korea's inviolable Tok Islet continues and urged the government to strongly counter Japan's incessant provocations.
 The organization formed a protest team and dispatched it to Japan on Feb. 21 with a view to checking the commemorations. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Headquarters of the Movement for Retaking History of Tok Islet also held a press conference in front of the building of the Ministry of Foreign Affairs and Trade in Seoul on Feb. 22 and demanded the government strongly cope with the reckless action of Japan. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The south Korean government in a commentary issued on the same day as regards Japan's commemorations clarified that the government will resolutely counter any attempt to encroach upon the dominium over Tok Islet, an inalienable territory of Korea.

Meeting of Officials in Field of Land and Environment Preservation Held 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, February 26 (KCNA) -- A meeting of officials in the field of land and environment preservation took place at the People's Palace of Culture Saturday.
 Present there were Premier of the Cabinet Pak Pong Ju, Secretary of the C.C., Workers' Party of Korea Kim Jung Rin and cabinet members, leading officials of ministries, national institutions and working people's organizations, leading officials of provincial, city and county party and power organs and officials of land and environment preservation and related sectors. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A report on reviewing the work of land management last year was made and then followed speeches at the meeting. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A reporter and speakers referred to the achievements in the work of land management including the planting of good kinds of trees such as pine-nut trees, larches and acacias in the area of at least 100,000 hectares and the paving of hundreds of kilometers of new roads last year, which they said are the precious fruition of the tireless leadership of Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They underscored the need to launch a dynamic campaign to spruce up the land of the country to suit the features of a great prosperous powerful country true to the party's Juche-based idea of land management in this significant year marking the 10th anniversary of Kim Jong Il's initiation of a powerful party and social campaign for land management. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They called upon all provinces, cities and counties to step up turning the country into a thick woodland ad greenery and the projects for preventing flood damage, holding fast to afforestation and river improvement as the main task of land management this year.
 They called for continuing to push forward the paving of new roads and their repair and management, sprucing up the capital city of Pyongyang and extensively building modern dwelling houses in provincial, city and county seats. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They called upon all sectors and units to set the objects of land construction so as to substantially help develop the national economy and improve the people's living standard and intensify the guidance to construction and supervision for it.
 They called upon provinces, cities and counties to build up well model units of land management and generalize them to carry on land management on a higher level.
 They stressed that all the officials should make positive contributions to planning and carrying on the preservation of land and environment in a big way and build up land in a revolutionary way to meet the requirements of the new century,  regarding the intention of Kim Jong Il as an absolute standard.

February 16 Celebrated in Peru 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, February 26 (KCNA) -- A national meeting and a book and photo exhibition were held at the building of the Peruvian Journalists' Association on Feb. 10 on the occasion of the holiday of February.
 Displayed in the venues of the functions were works of President Kim Il Sung and leader Kim Jong Il, Korean books and photos on the subject of "Kim Jong Il, Korea Today" and "Celebration of the 60th founding anniversary of the Workers' Party of Korea". &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there were leading officials of parties and organizations including the Peruvian-Korean Institute of Culture and Friendship, the Socialist Party of Peru, the Revolutionary Socialist Party of Peru, the Peruvian Communist Party and the Communist Party of Peru (Red Motherland)", members of organizations for study of the Juche idea and organizations of friendship and solidarity with the Korean people, political and public figures and masses from all walks of life. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present on invitation were the Korean ambassador to Peru and embassy officials.
 At the meeting speakers stressed that February 16 is the auspicious holiday of the Korean people as well as all peoples of the world. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is the global trend to deeply study and learn from the Songun politics, they said, adding that the unique Songun politics of  Kim Jong Il is kept deep in the hearts of the world people for its might, validity and vitality and dynamically pushes the world along the track of independence. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A letter to Kim Jong Il was adopted at the meeting.

Kim Jong Il's Work Published in Booklet in Peru 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, February 26 (KCNA) -- Leader Kim Jong Il's famous work "The Juche Philosophy Is an Original Revolutionary Philosophy" was brought out in booklet by the Publilaser Publishing House of Peru on Feb. 13.
 The work, published on July 26, Juche 85 (1996), clearly clarifies the scientific analysis of the time limitation of the preceding philosophy and the uniqueness of the Juche philosophy and the idea that the Juche philosophy serves as the revolutionary and political one of the Workers' Party of Korea. It specifies the matters of principle in study and explanation of the Juche philosophy. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The preface of the booklet says: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Juche philosophy, which made the most precious contribution to the socialist cause, finds its quintessence in the Juche idea founded by President Kim Il Sung, the eternal leader of the Korean people, and comprehensively systematized and enriched by leader Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 But for the Juche idea, the Korean people could not defend the socialist banner in the hard trials nor heroically beat back the incessant moves of the U.S. imperialists and their following forces for aggression and economic blockade against the DPRK.
 The Songun politics pursued by Kim Jong Il is based on the Juche idea.

Rodong Sinmun on Three-point Patriotic Movement 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, February 26 (KCNA) -- The idea and leadership of Kim Jong Il are now serving as a victorious banner which powerfully encourages the 70 million fellow countrymen in their nation-wide efforts to conduct the dynamic three-point patriotic movement under the banner of "By our nation itself".
 Rodong Sinmun today observes this in a signed article. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It says: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  This is clearly proved by the reality that the Korean nation is advancing this year, holding high the slogan "Let us vigorously forward the patriotic movement for independent reunification, peace against war and great national unity under the banner of 'by our nation itself!'". &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Kim Jong Il's idea and leadership are the driving force that helps all the fellow countrymen turn out in the road of independent reunification in the high spirit of national independence. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 His great idea of national independence opened the June 15 era of reunification advancing in the idea of "By our nation itself". The 70 million fellow countrymen are now vigorously conducting the movement for independent reunification across the country under the banner of "By our nation itself" in an effort to establish national sovereignty and national independence and cooperation are prevailing in the history of the nation. This proud reality is a brilliant fruition brought about by the embodiment of his great idea of national independence. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 His idea and leadership serve as a banner for encouraging the fellow countrymen in their struggle to frustrate the aggression and war moves of the bellicose forces at home and abroad and defend peace and security of the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The structure of confrontation between the Korean nation and the United States has been formed in the Korean Peninsula amid the daily growing struggle of the 70 million fellow countrymen for peace against war. This is proceeding from the confidence and pluck of the Korean nation encouraged by the great patriotic Songun politics which helps firmly defend national dignity and sovereignty and peace and security of the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 His idea and leadership are the great motive force to achieve national reconciliation and unity and strengthen the driving force of national reunification in every way. 
 The reconciliation and unity of the Korean nation has opened the new era of "By our nation itself" startling the world people thanks to his wide patriotic all-embracing politics. He leads whoever strives for national reunification with national conscience, irrespective of capitalist, army general or ruling stratum, to stand in the ranks of great national unity and embraces anyone who repents of wrong doings and intends to devote himself to the cause of national reunification even though he betrayed the nation and took a wrong road in the past.

Records of History Discovered in S. Korea
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, February 25 (KCNA) -- A large number of records of the government up to 1980 since the liberation of Korea were recently discovered in south Korea, KBS of south Korea said on Feb. 21.
 Among the more than 40,000 volumes of documents are "minutes of the State Council meetings" proving the fact that dictator Syngman Rhee obstructed the elimination of pro-Japanese elements. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 As already known, there was in south Korea the "special committee for investigation of traitors" inside the "Constituent Assembly" (the "National Assembly" at present) in 1948 whose mission was to investigate and punish the pro-Japanese elements who committed unpardonable acts of treachery during the Japanese imperialists' rule. However, the "special committee" ceased to exist without any success eight months after it started its activities in January 1949. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is said that the reason was explained in the "minutes of the State Council meetings" related to the "special committee." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is expected that if the relevant records are opened to the public they would be used as important basic information for the study of various cases and facts that still remain unclear and have strong impact on the campaign demanding a probe into the truth behind those cases and facts and compensation to the victims, the radio reported.

Joint Press Release between Delegations of Youth Organisations of North and South
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, February 25 (KCNA) -- A joint press release between the delegations of youth organizations of the north and the south of Korea was made public in Pyongyang on Friday.
 According to the joint press release, the south side's delegation of the youth committees of the Uri Party, the Democratic Party and the Democratic Workers' Party visited Pyongyang from Feb. 20 to 24, 2006 under the sponsorship of the youth and students sub-committee of the North Side's Committee for Implementing the June 15 Joint Declaration and the youth and students headquarters of the South Side's Committee.
 The first Pyongyang visit by the south side's delegation of youth committees of political parties after the division of Korea is a significant meeting of Korean youths in the north and the south,  masters of national destiny and future, which fully demonstrated at home and abroad the justness and vitality of the June 15 North-South Joint Declaration. 
 During its stay the south side's delegation of youth committees of political parties met with Kim Ki Nam, secretary of the C.C., the Workers' Party of Korea, held a joint meeting of youths in the north and the south for implementing the June 15 joint declaration with youths of the north side and had a meeting with officials of the Central Committee of the Kim Il Sung Socialist Youth League. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It also visited the old home in Mangyongdae, Kim Il Sung University, Kim Chaek University of Technology, the International Friendship Exhibition, the Tower of the Juche Idea, the Arch of Triumph, the King Tangun's Mausoleum, the King Tongmyong's Mausoleum and other places. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Youths in the north and the south agreed to take the lead in implementing the June 15 North-South Joint Declaration and fulfill their mission and role in preventing war and defending  peace in this land and developing inter-Korean relations by the efforts of the Korean nation itself. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Firmly affirming that they are a proud young generation in the June 15 era, they decided to achieve great national unity, transcending ideology, idea, political party and affiliation and develop multifarious cooperation and exchanges between youths in the north and the south.

Kim Jong Il Gives Field Guidance to Munchon Kumgang Smeltery
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, February 25 (KCNA) -- Kim Jong Il, general secretary of the Workers' Party of Korea and chairman of the National Defence Commission of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea, gave field guidance to the Munchon Kumgang Smeltery.
 After looking round the room devoted to the history of the smeltery, he went round the liquefying shop, zinc electrolyzing shop and various other processes of the smeltery to learn in detail about its technical equipment and production there.
 He was greatly satisfied to learn that the workers of the smeltery intensely loyal to the Party and the revolution have waged a vigorous drive to increase the production of non-ferrous metals and spruced up their work places as required by the era of Songun.
 It is very good that the smeltery has made strenuous efforts to modernize and scientize the production processes, thereby completely freeing the workers from difficult and labor consuming work, he said, underscoring the need to fully meet the requirements of the Juche idea for giving primary consideration to man in any work.
 Noting that the workers of the smeltery have upheld the Party with pure conscience and sense of obligation, firmly maintaining the consistent working class stand and steadfastly abiding by the principle of socialism even under the difficult and complicated situation and thus strikingly demonstrated the invincible might of the heroic working class of Korea, he highly appreciated their life totally dedicated to the prosperity of the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He set forth tasks to be fulfilled by the smeltery. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The demand for non-ferrous metals is further increasing as the socialist economic construction is developing in depth, he noted, calling for increasing the production and supply of non-ferrous metals badly needed by it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Saying that it is necessary for the smeltery to plan and undertake any work in a big and bold manner as it is a promising enterprise capable of producing a variety of non-ferrous metals and basic chemical products in order to turn it into a giant non-ferrous metal production centre in a brief span of time, he underlined the necessity to continue dynamically pushing ahead with the work to put the production processes on a modern and scientific basis to this end. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He called for further improving the supply service for the workers.
 He stressed the need for all leading officials of the factories and enterprises to become servants for the workers and take deep care of their living down to all details as the DPRK has built a society for the working class. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He expressed expectation and conviction that the workers of the smeltery would successfully perform their role as a pacemaker in implementing the WPK's economic strategy. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He was accompanied by Ri Jae Il and Kim Tong Un, first vice department directors of the C.C., WPK.
